==English==

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ræŋk/

===Adjective===
'''rank'''

# having a very strong and bad [[odor]]
# highly offensive; disgusting

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[löyhkäävä]], [[lemuava]]
*German: [[stinkend]] (1), [[ekelhaft]] (2)
{{mid}}
*Swedish: [[stank]] (1), [[vämjelig]] (2)
{{bottom}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# position of a person, place or thing in relation to others based on a shared property such as physical [[location]], [[population]] or [[quality]]
#: ''Based on your test scores, you have a rank of 23.''
# a level in an [[organization]] such as the [[military]]
#: ''Private First Class (PFC) is the lowest rank in the Marines.''
# The lines or rows of people in an organization
# One of the horizontal lines of squares on a [[chessboard]]

